@startuml
title FIG-01-01. Model, view and reality

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam rectangle {
  BackgroundColor #F2F7F5
  BorderColor #2F5E4E
  FontColor #111111
  RoundCorner 8
}
skinparam arrow {
  Color #555555
  FontColor #333333
}

left to right direction

rectangle "Real situation\n\nPeople, systems, data,\nprocesses, constraints\nand goals" as reality
rectangle "Architecture model\n\nA purposeful simplification\nthat keeps the facts needed\nfor a decision" as model
rectangle "Business view\n\nWhat outcome and\nwho is involved?" as business
rectangle "Software view\n\nWhat systems and\ninterfaces matter?" as software
rectangle "Deployment view\n\nWhere does it run\nand operate?" as deployment
rectangle "Decision or action\n\nChoose, explain, review,\nchange or govern" as decision

reality -right-> model : select relevant facts
model -right-> business : create view
model -right-> software : create view
model -right-> deployment : create view
business -right-> decision : inform
software -right-> decision : inform
deployment -right-> decision : inform
business -[hidden]down-> software
software -[hidden]down-> deployment
decision -[dashed]-> reality : changes what exists

note bottom of model
  A model is not the whole reality.
  It is useful because it leaves
  irrelevant detail out.
end note

@enduml
